UTAH COUNTY RECORDER
2003 Jan 31 10:29 am FEE 12.00 BY BLS
RECORDED FOR JACOBS, JOHN
NOTICE OF LIEN
TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN;
A-KRETE, INC ., 253 South 100 West, American Fork, Utah 84003, (801-756-5360),
(DOPL # 363360-5501 and ULRF # 363360-5551) lien claimant, acting through its
authorized agent, John H. Jacobs, Attorney at Law, hereby holds and claims a mechanic's
lien, pursuant to Section 38-1-1, et. sec ., Utah Code Annotated, 1953 (as amended 2001),
upon the property and improvements thereon owned or reputed to be owned by STAN
WEST, 1943 S. 460 W ., Lehi, Utah 84043, located in Lehi, Utah 84043, more particularly
described as follows, to-wit:
Lot 32, Plat B, North Lake PRD Subdivision, according to the official plat thereof as
filed in the office of the Utah County Recorders Office.Parcel # 47:218:0032
Lien Claimant claims and holds a lien upon the above described property for amounts
owing for furnishing materials and labor upon, or in connection with the improvement of,
said real property.
The lien claimant was employed by RANDAL QUALITY
CONSTRUCTION, LLC, 851 West 260 South, Orem, Utah 84058, or furnished the aforesaid
materials or labor to said company. Lien Claimant has made demand for payment, but the
owner has refused and continues to refuse payment. The outstanding balance due and owing
lien claimant includes the principal amount due for the cost of the materials or services
provided along with interest, costs, and attorney's fees.
A-Krete, Inc. first furnished the said materials on October 29th, 2002 and the last date
services or materials were furnished was November 20th, 2002.
Protection Against Liens and Civil Action
NOTICE IS HEREBY PROVIDED in accordance with Section 38-11-108 of the Utah
Code that under Utah Law an "Owner" may be protected against liens being maintained
against an "Owner-occupied residence" and from other civil action being maintained to
recover monies owed for "qualified services" performed or provided by suppliers and
subcontractors as a part of this contract, if and only if the following conditions are satisfied:
(1) the owner entered into a written contract with an original contractor, a factory
built housing retailer, or a real estate developer;
(2) the original contractor was properly licensed or exempt from licensure under Title
58, Chapter 55, Utah Construction Trades Licensing Act at the time the contract was
executed; and
(3) the owner paid in full the original contractor, factory built housing retailer, or real
estate developer or their successors or assigns in accordance with the written contract and
any written or oral amendments to the contract. (Utah Administrative Code R156-38-108)
John H. Jacobs, Attorney for
A-KRETE, INC.
